roadmap_conventions:
  series_cover_set:
    requirement: The complete set of paperback AND hardcover full wraps (front · spine · back) for ALL
      volumes in a series is produced AS ONE BATCH, before the first volume's human review — not one-at-a-time
      at final-artifact assembly.
    why: Consistency across the series (one design language, palette, typography, spine system) locked
      in a single pass; eliminates the one-at-a-time / days-apart DRIFT KM flagged. KM reviews each book
      WITH its final wrap in hand, not a placeholder.
    workflow_change: 'SUPERSEDES the per-title late-cover in WORKFLOW step 20: covers move from ''built
      at final publishable-artifact assembly, per title'' -> ''series cover-set batch, Phase 1, pre-human-review.''
      Step 20 then only assembles the already-made wrap. (WORKFLOW.md canon edit = Tiger''s vault-fold,
      per GB spec.)'
    deliverable: 'per series: pb wrap + hc wrap per volume (correct trim/bleed/spine-width per page count),
      a shared cover-design spec, + KM ratify of the SET (consistency check across all volumes at once).'
    backfill: S2 NOW (Tiger building Vol 1 covers - do the full 5-vol pb+hc set in the same pass); apply
      S3->S9 + future at series activation. S1 already published.
    gate: series cover-set ratified by KM (as a set) before any volume in that series enters human review.
  series_description:
    requirement: 'Every public series carries a `series_description` block: {artifact (path to SERIES_DESCRIPTION_KDP.md
      in the vault), reading_order (ordered|unordered), status, gate}.'
    workflow_position: Phase −1 deliverable (alongside series-lock + editorial-board-signoff) — drafted
      GB, polished via G, ratified KM; a series's FIRST volume does not publish until its series_description
      status = ready/pasted.
    kdp_ready: 'REQUIRED at SERIES CREATION (KM 2026-06-15): the artifact must carry the KDP-ready HTML
      version (KDP-supported tags only: p/b/i/ul/li/br/h4) for direct paste into the KDP series-detail
      Description field, PLUS reading-order + the short alternate. ''series description etc required to
      load to KDP'' = the full KDP series-setup payload, authored when the series is created, not at first-publish.'
  seeit_figures:
    requirement: 'Per volume, the figure/visual workflow is TWO-STAGE in this order: (1) DETAILED figures
      authored + pushed to the seeit interactive surface FIRST (full-resolution, full-detail, interactive/zoomable);
      (2) THEN the SIMPLIFIED, print-legible book visuals derived from them (enlarged type, reduced detail)
      embedded in the manuscript. Detail lives in seeit; the book carries the simplified version + a pointer
      to seeit.'
    why: How V1 shipped (seeit_review_v1.0.md + 22 print-legible book figures; detail moved to seeit).
      Print can't carry full detail legibly; seeit is the detail home. Doing seeit-first means the book
      visuals are DERIVED from the authoritative detailed set, not re-drawn — one source, no drift.
    quality_bar: 'MATCH V1''s DESIGN SYSTEM, not just its palette (KM 2026-06-15, caught a sharp quality
      decline in the first V2-V5 pass). V1''s vol_01/v1.0/generate_images.py + its 34 images are the REFERENCE
      BAR. Every figure must reproduce V1''s editorial composition: (1) balanced title sizing with a gold
      accent RULE under the title (not an oversized title crowding the frame); (2) structured/layered
      composition — numbered tokens, callouts, sidebars, framed boxes where the content warrants — NOT
      bare ellipses/stacked-boxes on white; (3) intentional density (V1-level), not slide-clipart minimalism;
      (4) NO TEXT OVERLAP/COLLISION — title/subtitle must never overlap content (the V4 fig_3_1 title↔box
      collision was a real defect). RENDER CHECK: a no-overlap/legibility pass per figure. The palette
      (navy/gold/green, 300 DPI, ≤4.75in) is necessary but NOT sufficient — the bar is V1''s design quality.'
    rail_position: 'Per-volume rail step (with deterministic-render / Gate 6): seeit detailed figures
      → seeit_review_<v>.md, THEN simplified book figures → manuscript + render-legibility pass. Required
      to reach the V1 bar.'
    learning_surface_system: 'RATIFIED scope (KM 2026-06-15) — a finished S2 volume = V1''s full HANDS-ON
      LEARNING SYSTEM, not manuscript+PNGs: (1) in-book ''See It Work — Run It Yourself'' section (per-chapter:
      what-you-see + runnable command + walkthrough link); (2) DETAILED seeit charts (figure_X_Y.svg)
      authored FIRST → BOOK charts derived (figure_X_Y_book.svg → PNG) at V1 quality; (3) _figure_manifest.json;
      (4) real seeit_review fidelity gate (every command resolves); (5) live /seeit/s2v{n}-* walkthrough
      pages. Full scope: artifacts/GB_S2_SeeIt_LearningSurface_FULL_SCOPE_2026-06-15.md. BUILD ORDER =
      detailed-first (detailed seeit charts → derive book charts).'
    live_deploy_gate: 'PUBLISH GATE = OPTION 1 (KM-ratified 2026-06-15, matches V1''s actual ship): a
      volume publishes once the in-book See-It-Work section + detailed→book charts (V1 quality) + real
      fidelity gate are complete AND in-book links resolve to the LIVE /seeit BASE (six-sov.com/seeit,
      deployed mangumcfo/six-sov.com). The per-chapter DEEP walkthrough pages (/seeit/s2v{n}-*) FAST-FOLLOW
      at release (V1''s deep pages were 404 at review, live at launch — not a book-text defect). Generating
      figures in the VAULT is NOT enough; the live /seeit base must resolve. Deploy owner = Tiger (six-sov.com
