  source: artifacts/GB_Forward_Architecture_Synthesis_2026-06-14.md
  first_wall: token_economics_plus_human_attention
  ranked_walls:
  - token_economics
  - human_gate_throughput
  - monolithic_catalog
  - parity_at_scale
  - ledger_growth
  - single_node
  - merkle_memory
  build_now:
  - storage_interfaces:
    - ledger_gateway_have_it
    - catalog_gateway
    - parity_query_gateway
  - partition_keys:
    - series_id
    - book_id
    - principal_id
    - node_id
    - obligation_id
    - epoch
  - delta_first_pipeline: books declare deltas; audits run on deltas; full sweeps become sampled/exceptional
  - catalog_as_query_interface:
    - catalog.query(predicate)
    - get(id)
    - list_by_series(id)
    - changed_since(epoch)
  - ledger_segmentation_spec:
    - segment
    - checkpoint_snapshot
    - current_state_index
    - merkle_root_per_segment
    - global_root_over_segments
  - cost_model:
    - tokens_per_book
    - tokens_per_series_template
    - tokens_per_delta
    - tokens_per_exception
    - tokens_per_full_sweep
  - series_inheritance_rule: a volume inherits its series boards/specs/renderability unless explicitly
      overridden
  defer:
  - distributed_db
  - full_sharded_ledger_impl
  - multi_node_consensus
  - complex_federation_routing
  - 1M_scale_ui
  - autonomous_publishing_factory
  unification: audit HIGH#1 VerifiableMemory O(n^2) fix == merkle scale pattern (leaf_log->segment_root->checkpoint_root->global_commitment);
    ONE build
  scaling_model: federation_of_sovereign_pens
  scaling_model_note: scale to 1M = REPLICATE the sovereign node (CONSTITUTION sec9 Profiles/forkable),
    NOT loosen the gate. Federation members become writers; each runs the UNCHANGED constitution on their
    own node; each is the human pen for their own novelty. human-in-loop-for-novelty preserved BY CONSTRUCTION
    (many pens, not a thinner gate). What scales sublinearly = inherited LGP layer (guards+templates+specs+receipt-format)
    that travels between nodes + verifiable locally (no central hub = no sovereignty SPOF).
  constitution_change_required: NONE
  withdrawn:
  - human_gate_at_scale_amendment: WITHDRAWN per KM 2026-06-14 -- diluted sovereignty. Replaced by node-replication
      (forkable constitution per writer).
  catalog_as_query_note: NOT a constitution item; per-node interface-now/backend-later via 3-phase governed
    transition (g_ratification_guards.catalog_3phase_transition)
  guards_now_cross_node: the 3 G-guards become CROSS-NODE inheritance protection (Gate-Escape on each
    node's own chain; no-invisible-inheritance carries parent_policy_id+inherited_version+escape_count
    between nodes; inheritance_drift is now a federation-level risk)
  dual_witness_ratified: G + Lumen both ratified v2 (federation-of-sovereign-pens, no canon change) 2026-06-14
  three_cases:
    batch_expansion: 'KM-authored multi-volume wave (e.g. ERP 30-100) -- valid under UNCHANGED constitution:
      human-ratified series arch + visible inherited templates + delta review + exception escalation +
      EVERY book its own seal'
    federation_growth: thousands of sovereign operator-nodes; each human pen for own novelty; inherited+locally-verified,
      never centrally imposed
    translation_derivative: 'DERIVATIVE class not new novelty (unless adds interpretation/jurisdictional/cultural
      reframing): source_hash->target_lang->process->human linguistic review->derivative_seal->link_to_original'
  authorship_rule: a batch may inherit governance, but authorship responsibility cannot be batched away
    -- one human pen per novelty always
  1M_is: capacity_horizon_not_production_target
  build_now_converged:
  - signed_inheritance_objects
  - batch_scope_receipt
  - per_book_delta_receipt
  - translation_derivative_class
  - local_verifier_path_source_inheritance_delta_seal
  - partition_keys
  - ledger_segment_snapshot_spec
  near_term_proving_ground: 'THE ERP ARC (already scoped): S3 Programmable Sovereign ERP (4-vol constitutional
    ROOT) -> S5 Full Production ERP (G 32-title projection). S5 titles ALREADY declare inheritance (''overlaps
    Series 3 Vol X'') => the inheritance map exists. This is the literal series-level-inheritance proving
    ground.'
  erp_inheritance_mapping: 'signed_inheritance_object per S5 title: parent_policy_id = its S3 root volume;
    inherited = constitutional ERP pattern/template; delta = vertical/functional specialization. Makes
    the 32-title S5 wave SUBLINEAR (derive from root) AND honest (no-invisible-inheritance: each title
    declares what it inherited + from where).'
  erp_near_term_gate: 'S5 expansion UNBLOCKS once S3 V4 fills (V4 outline_PARTIAL: Ch3-5 Manufacturing/Electronics/3rd-pattern
    STUBBED by G, surfaced to Atrium). Critical path: S3 V4 fill -> S5 concept doc (Tiger+G) -> inheritance
    objects designed against real S3->S5 map -> S5 extrusion.'
  open_federation_question: how do N sovereign human-pen nodes share an inherited LGP layer WITHOUT a
    central authority -- forkable profiles + signed inheritance objects + locally-runnable bl-verify (see
    G_ASK_forward_architecture_scale_2026-06-14_v2.md)
  g_ratification_guards:
    gate_escape_is_material_obligation: inherited governance valid only while escalation predicates active+monitored+receipt-bound;
      any failure-to-escalate = Gate Escape = material obligation
    no_invisible_inheritance: 'every inherited governance object carries: [parent_policy_id, inherited_version,
      override_status, last_validation_epoch, escape_count]'
    catalog_3phase_transition: P1 YAML canon + gateway reads YAML; P2 dual-read/compare YAML==query-store
      (loud divergence); P3 KM ratifies -> query-store canon, YAML becomes export/view; write-authority
      declared+singular+receipt-bound at every phase
    named_new_disease: inheritance_drift
  yagni_law: no new abstraction unless it removes a future rewrite OR reduces present propagation debt
